Remeadiation for Sample 1:
Prefer using standard language semantics where possible. This compliant solution uses the vector.clear() method, which removes all elements:

public void useVector(int count) { 
  try {
    for (int n = 0; n < count; n++) {
      vector.add(Integer.toString(n));
    }
    // ...
  } finally {
    vector.clear(); // Clear the vector
  }
}




Remeadiation for Sample 2: 
Use weak references to allow timely garbage collection:

// ...
private Map<SSLSocket, InetAddress> m = Collections.synchronizedMap(
  new WeakHashMap<SSLSocket, InetAddress>()
);

